void ObitCArray2DCenter (  ObitCArray *  in  ) 
 

Public: Convert a half plane 2D "center at edges" array to proper order.

The first and second halves of each column are swaped. This is needed for the peculiar order of FFTs. This uses the FFTW convention that half plane complex arrays have the "short" (i.e. n/2+1) dimension first.

Parameters:
in Half plane complex 2D array to reorder
Returns:
the new object.

void ObitCArray2DCenterFull (  ObitCArray *  in  ) 
 

Public: Convert a full plane 2D "center at edges" array to proper order.

The first and second halves of each column are swaped. This is needed for the peculiar order of FFTs. This uses the FFTW convention that half plane complex arrays have the "short" (i.e. n/2+1) dimension first.

Parameters:
in Full plane complex 2D array to reorder
Returns:

ObitCArray* ObitCArrayAddConjg (  ObitCArray *  in,
olong  numConjCol
) 
 

Public: Add conjugate columns to half plane complex image.

Only does 2D half plane complex images. This uses the FFTW convention that half plane complex arrays have the "short" (i.e. n/2+1) dimension first. Thus rows must have added columns.

Parameters:
in Input array
numConjCol How many conjugate columns to add.
Returns:
the new object.
